Brachiaria radicans

   Authority Napper
   Family Liliopsida:Commelinidae:Cyperales:Gramineae
   Synonyms Brachiaria arrecta (T. Durand & Schinz) Stent, Brachiaria
   latifolia Stapf
   Common names tanner grass, tanner-grass (En), pasto taner, pasto
   tanner, taner, tanner (Sp), bracquiaria do brejo, capim tanner (Pt)
   Editor
   Ecocrop code 3813

   Notes
   BRIEF DESCRIPTION A stoloniferous grass growing 100-150 cm high, with
   glabrous culms, rotting at the lower nodes, and lanceolate leaf-blades
   up to 15 cm long and 12 mm wide. USES Used for pasture. GROWING PERIOD
   Fast-growing, summer, perennial grass. COMMON NAMES Tanner grass.
   FURTHER INF Scientific synonym: B. latifolia. Tanner grass is common in
   swampy and seasonal flooded grassland. In Tanzania, it can be found at
   elevations from 1300-2000 m. It does not tolerate drought. May yield
   about 13 t/ha of green matter three months after planting. Some anaemia
   has been reported in horses and sheep grazing tanner grass.

   Sources
   [10]Grassland Index
   [11]Grassland Index - In Ecocrop as synonym Brachiaria radicans
   Skerman P 1990 pp 254 [DRA, RAIN, DEP, TEXT, PH, FER, LIMITS]

